# Implementation Plan: `show-session` subcommand

## 1. Module layout

Two new files, plus small edits to `src/main.rs` and `Cargo.toml`.

### `/home/wink/data/prgs/rust/vc-x1/src/transcript.rs` — parsing + typed layer (command-agnostic)

Module header (`//!`): "Claude Code session transcript (.jsonl) parsing: serde_json is used only as text → `Value`; hand-written extraction builds the typed layer; unknown fields ride along in the retained `Value`."

Types:

```rust
/// A parsed session transcript: every parseable line, in file order.
pub struct Transcript {
    /// All entries, including ones the conversation view hides.
    pub entries: Vec<Entry>,
    /// Malformed lines: (1-based line number, parse error text).
    pub malformed: Vec<(usize, String)>,
}

/// One parsed JSONL line.
pub struct Entry {
    /// 1-based line number in the source file.
    pub line_no: usize,
    /// Common metadata shared across entry types (all optional-tolerant).
    pub meta: EntryMeta,
    /// Classified payload.
    pub kind: EntryKind,
    /// The full original parsed line; unknown fields ride along here.
    pub raw: serde_json::Value,
}

/// Common top-level fields; every one degrades to None/false when absent.
pub struct EntryMeta {
    pub uuid: Option<String>,
    pub parent_uuid: Option<String>,
    /// Raw ISO-8601 string, unparsed (chrono has no parse feature).
    pub timestamp: Option<String>,
    pub session_id: Option<String>,
    pub is_sidechain: bool,
    pub is_meta: bool,
    pub cwd: Option<String>,
}

/// Classified payload by top-level `type`.
pub enum EntryKind {
    /// type=user: typed prompt (content was a string) or tool results
    /// (content was an array) — both normalized to blocks.
    User {
        content: Vec<ContentBlock>,
        /// "typed" for real human prompts (promptSource field).
        prompt_source: Option<String>,
    },
    /// type=assistant: one JSONL line per content block in practice,
    /// but modeled as a Vec to be shape-agnostic.
    Assistant {
        content: Vec<ContentBlock>,
        /// message.id — lets the renderer merge blocks of one API turn.
        message_id: Option<String>,
    },
    /// type=system (subtype e.g. "turn_duration").
    System { subtype: Option<String> },
    /// Everything else (mode, permission-mode, file-history-*, ai-title,
    /// last-prompt, attachment, progress, queue-operation, unknown…).
    Other { entry_type: String },
}

/// One block of message.content.
pub enum ContentBlock {
    Text { text: String },
    Thinking { thinking: String },
    ToolUse { id: String, name: String, input: serde_json::Value },
    ToolResult { tool_use_id: String, text: String, is_error: bool },
    /// Unrecognized block type — kept for counting, never rendered.
    Other { block_type: String },
}
```

Design notes for later cycles: `uuid`/`parent_uuid` in `EntryMeta` plus retained `raw` mean cross-file following (leafUuid, sidechain agent files, compaction) can be added by walking `Transcript.entries` and re-extracting from `raw` — no restructuring. `Other { entry_type }` keeps every line countable and indexable.

Functions:

```rust
/// Parse a whole file. Errors only on I/O; malformed lines are recorded.
pub fn parse_file(path: &Path) -> Result<Transcript, Box<dyn std::error::Error>>;

/// Parse transcript text (unit-testable without files).
pub fn parse_str(text: &str) -> Transcript;

/// Parse one line into an Entry (used by parse_str; unit-test target).
fn parse_line(line_no: usize, line: &str) -> Result<Entry, String>;

// Value-extraction helpers (private; the "hand-written extraction" layer):
/// String field at key, as owned Option<String>.
fn get_str(v: &Value, key: &str) -> Option<String>;
/// Bool field, false when absent or non-bool.
fn get_bool(v: &Value, key: &str) -> bool;
/// message.content normalized: string → single Text block; array → per-block.
fn extract_content(message: &Value) -> Vec<ContentBlock>;
/// tool_result content: string, or array of {type:text} blocks joined.
fn tool_result_text(content: &Value) -> String;
```

`tool_result_text` handles both observed shapes (plain string; array of text blocks). `parse_line` never panics; missing `type` → `Other { entry_type: "<none>" }`. Truncated last line falls out naturally as one malformed entry.

Tests as sibling file `src/transcript/tests.rs` via `#[cfg(test)] #[path = "transcript/tests.rs"] mod tests;` (the `src/common.rs` / `src/common/tests.rs` pattern).

### `/home/wink/data/prgs/rust/vc-x1/src/show_session.rs` — command + renderer

Follows `src/validate_todo.rs` shape exactly:

```rust
#[derive(Args, Debug)]
pub struct ShowSessionArgs {
    /// Session transcript .jsonl file to display
    #[arg(value_name = "FILE")]
    pub file: PathBuf,
    /// Show thinking blocks
    #[arg(long)]
    pub thinking: bool,
    /// Show tool results (truncated) under each tool call
    #[arg(long)]
    pub tools: bool,
    /// Show meta-injected user lines and system entries
    #[arg(long)]
    pub meta: bool,
}

pub struct ShowSessionParams {
    pub file: PathBuf,
    pub opts: RenderOptions,
}

/// What the conversation view reveals beyond the default.
pub struct RenderOptions { pub thinking: bool, pub tools: bool, pub meta: bool }

impl From<&ShowSessionArgs> for ShowSessionParams { ... }   // total, like validate-todo
impl SubcommandRunner for ShowSessionArgs { type Params = ShowSessionParams; ... }

pub fn show_session(_ctx: &Context, params: &ShowSessionParams)
    -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>>;
```

Renderer as pure private functions returning `String`/`Vec<String>` (unit-testable, printed via `info!` by `show_session`):

```rust
/// Render the whole conversation; also returns hidden/skipped counts.
fn render(t: &Transcript, opts: &RenderOptions) -> (Vec<String>, RenderStats);
/// One-line gist of a tool_use input.
fn tool_use_gist(name: &str, input: &Value) -> String;
/// "HH:MM:SS" slice of an ISO timestamp (safe .get(11..19), fallback raw).
fn short_time(ts: Option<&str>) -> String;
/// Counters for the trailing summary line.
struct RenderStats { shown: usize, hidden_thinking: usize, hidden_tool_results: usize,
                     hidden_meta: usize, skipped_other: usize, malformed: usize }
```

### Wiring (small edits)
- `src/main.rs`: `mod show_session;` + `mod transcript;` in the mod list; `Commands::ShowSession(show_session::ShowSessionArgs)` variant with a `long_about` describing default hiding + reveal flags; one `Commands::ShowSession(args) => args.dispatch(&ctx)` match arm.
- Clap kebab-cases the variant to `show-session` automatically.

## 2. Renderer design

Conversation view (default):

```
=== user 04:17:09 ===                      ← bold via common::bold
Let's do todo 1, move notes/todo.md ./TODO.md

=== assistant 04:17:15 ===
I'll start by reading the top of `notes/todo.md` ...
  [tool] Read: notes/todo.md (offset=0, limit=60)
```

Rules:
- Role header emitted only when the rendered role changes OR (assistant) `message_id` changes — collapses the one-line-per-block JSONL shape into visual turns. Header uses `common::bold` + `short_time`.
- User entries whose blocks are all ToolResult produce no user turn by default; with `--tools` each result renders indented under the conversation as `  [result] <first line> … (+K lines)` (cap ~10 lines / err flag shown as `[result:error]`).
- `tool_use_gist`: special-case well-known tools — `Bash` → first line of `input.command`; `Read`/`Write`/`Edit` → `input.file_path`; fallback → compact `key=value` pairs of string inputs, truncated to ~100 chars with `…`. Always one line.
- Thinking hidden by default; `--thinking` renders them dimmed-style prefix `  [thinking]` followed by indented text (use `common::indent_body`).
- Meta user lines (`isMeta:true`), `System` entries, and empty-text blocks hidden by default; `--meta` reveals them as `--- system turn_duration 04:24:07 ---` / meta text.
- Sidechain entries (`isSidechain:true`): hidden by default, revealed by `--meta` in v1 (a dedicated flag is a later cycle alongside sidechain-file following).
- No text wrapping in v1 (terminal wraps; `max_term_width` only affects help). Only one-liners truncate.
- Trailing summary line, always: `show-session: N turns shown; hidden: X thinking, Y tool results, Z meta/system; skipped: W bookkeeping entries; M malformed lines` (omit zero clauses).

Recommended v1 flag set: just `--thinking`, `--tools`, `--meta`. Defer `--raw`, ranges, and a `--all` shorthand to the linking/index cycles — three orthogonal reveal flags is coherent and small.

## 3. Unparseable/unknown handling

- Malformed line (bad JSON, or top-level not an object): `warn!("show-session: line {n}: {err}")` → stderr with `warn:` prefix (logging.rs routes Warn to stderr, always enabled), recorded in `Transcript.malformed`, processing continues. Truncated final live-session line hits this path; exit code stays 0.
- Unknown/unmodeled `type` values: parsed into `EntryKind::Other`, silently skipped by the renderer, counted in `RenderStats.skipped_other` and the summary line.
- Missing fields inside known types: every extraction is `Option`/default — a user entry without `message` renders as nothing but still counts.
- Only hard error: unreadable file — `format!("cannot read {}: {e}", …).into()` like validate-todo.
- No `unwrap`/`expect`; all slicing via `.get(..)` with fallbacks (project lint).

## 4. Cargo.toml

```toml
serde_json = "1"
```

Default features (they're just `std`). Pulls `serde` as a library dep — accepted per the binding decisions; no `derive` feature anywhere. No chrono change: timestamps stay raw strings sliced for display (chrono here has no parse/format features, and adding them isn't needed for v1).

## 5. Test plan

Unit — `src/transcript/tests.rs` (inline JSON string fixtures):
- typed user prompt (string content) → `User` + one Text block, `prompt_source == Some("typed")`, meta fields populated;
- assistant text / tool_use / thinking lines → correct `ContentBlock` variants; tool_use keeps `name` and `input` Value;
- user tool_result with string content and with array-of-text content → `tool_result_text` joins correctly; `is_error` extraction;
- `isMeta` / `isSidechain` flags land in `EntryMeta`;
- unknown type → `Other{entry_type}`; missing `type`; empty line skipped;
- `parse_str` with a truncated last line → entry count right, one `malformed` record with correct line_no;
- `raw` retains unknown fields (assert `entry.raw["gitBranch"]` still readable).

Unit — `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` in `src/show_session.rs`:
- `tool_use_gist` for Bash (multi-line command → first line), Read (file_path), unknown tool (truncation);
- `short_time` on valid ISO, short string, None;
- `render` on a tiny synthetic `Transcript`: header collapsing across same-message assistant blocks, thinking hidden/shown, tool result hidden/shown, meta hidden/shown, stats counts.

Integration — new `tests/cli_show_session.rs` using `CliFixture` (`mod common;`):
- Fixture written into `fx.base` as e.g. `session.jsonl` (~10 lines): mode line, typed user prompt, assistant thinking + text + tool_use (three lines, same message id), user tool_result, system turn_duration, ai-title, isMeta user line, and a final truncated line (write with no trailing `}`).
- `run_ok(fx.cmd().arg("show-session").arg(&file))`: stdout contains prompt text and assistant text, contains `[tool] `, does NOT contain thinking text or tool_result body; stderr contains one `warn:` for the truncated line.
- `--thinking --tools --meta` run: hidden content now present.
- `run_err` on a missing file: stderr contains "cannot read".

## 6. Step ladder (2 commits)

- **-1: transcript parsing + typed layer.** `Cargo.toml` serde_json dep; new `src/transcript.rs` + `src/transcript/tests.rs`; `mod transcript;` in main.rs. Nothing user-visible yet; the module compiles with `#[allow(dead_code)]` on not-yet-used items only if needed (prefer making `parse_str`/types `pub` and exercised by tests so clippy stays clean). Compiles, fmt/clippy/test green.
- **-2: show-session command + renderer + CLI wiring.** New `src/show_session.rs` (Args/Params/runner + renderer + in-module tests); `Commands::ShowSession` variant + dispatch arm + long_about; `tests/cli_show_session.rs` with the fixture; drop any temporary allows from -1.

(If the cycle prefers three rungs: split -2 into renderer-with-unit-tests and CLI-wiring-plus-integration-tests; two is my recommendation since the renderer only becomes exercisable end-to-end with the wiring.)

## Risks / open questions

- **Header collapsing heuristic**: grouping by consecutive role + assistant `message_id` matches observed data; interleaved sidechain lines (when later revealed) may split turns oddly — acceptable for v1, revisit in the sidechain cycle.
- **Empty thinking blocks** exist in real data (`"thinking": ""`); render nothing even under `--thinking` but still count, to avoid blank turns.
- **Large files** (~65k lines total across sessions; single files are a few MB): whole-file `read_to_string` is fine; streaming line-by-line via `BufRead` is a drop-in change inside `parse_file` if ever needed.
- **`session_id` vs `sessionId`** both appear top-level; extraction should try `sessionId` then `session_id`.
- **Open question for later cycles**: whether `Transcript` should own a `HashMap<uuid, index>` — deliberately deferred; `Vec<Entry>` with uuids in `meta` supports adding it without API breakage.

